SIMPLE: pastel
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pastel
<hw>Pas"tel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.; cf. It.
<ets>pastello</ets>. Cf. <er>Pastil</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
crayon made of a paste composed of a color ground with gum water.</def>
<altsp>[Sometimes incorrectly written <asp>pastil</asp>.]</altsp>
⟦ldquo⟧Charming heads in <xex>pastel</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>W.
Black.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant affording a blue dye; the
woad (<spn>Isatis tinctoria</spn>); also, the dye itself.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><--3. a drawing using pastel, or of a pastel shade. 4. the art or
process of drawing with pastels. 5. any of various light or pale colors.
6. a light literary work, as a sketch. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paster</ent>⟦br⟧
